HEADWORD: Pompeian
<hw>Pom*pe"ian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Pompeianus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to, or characteristic
of, <city>Pompeii</city>, an ancient city of Italy, buried by an
eruption of Vesuvius in 79 <sc>a. d.</sc>, and partly uncovered by
modern excavations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

